				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$0\le s < 3/2$$\end{document}. Kobayashi and Tsuda [28] obtained the global existence and time decay rates of solutions to the compressible Navier–Stokes–Korteweg system under critical condition. Moreover, for the initial value problem of the isentropic compressible Navier–Stokes–Korteweg system, the large-time behavior around nonlinear wave patterns such as the stationary wave, the contact discontinuity wave and the rarefaction wave has been studied. More precisely, the stability of stationary solutions of the multi-dimensional isentropic compressible Navier–Stokes–Korteweg equations was studied by Li [35], and Wang and Wang [53] in the case with a external force, under the assumption that the states at far fields ±∞\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
