				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\pm \infty $$\end{document} are equal. Later, Chen [3] and Li and Luo [36] discussed asymptotic stability of the rarefaction waves for the one-dimensional compressible fluid models of Korteweg type with different states at far fields. Chen, et al. [4] also showed asymptotic stability of the rarefaction waves for the one-dimensional compressible Navier–Stokes–Korteweg system with large initial data. Li and Zhu [38] further showed the asymptotic stability of the rarefaction wave with vacuum for the one-dimensional compressible Navier–Stokes–Korteweg equations. Chen, He and Zhao [6] studied the nonlinear stability of traveling wave solutions for the one-dimensional compressible Navier–Stokes–Korteweg equations.

